# 8. What is Rebase?

Rebase means

> Replay my commits on top of another branch.

Suppose

```text
A
 \
  B
```

Meanwhile

```text
A──C
```

Now

```bash
git rebase main
```

Result

```text
A──C──B'
```

Notice

B becomes

```text
B'
```

A brand new commit.

---

# 9. Why B becomes B'?

Original B says

```text
Parent = A
```

After rebase

Git wants

```text
Parent = C
```

Git cannot edit B.

So it creates

```text
B'
```

which has

```text
Parent = C
```

Different parent

↓

Different SHA

↓

Different commit

