# 10. Merge vs Rebase

### Merge

```text
A
├──B
└──C

↓

        M
       / \
      B   C
```

History preserved.

Creates Merge Commit.

---

### Rebase

```text
A
├──B
└──C

↓

A──C──B'
```

History rewritten.

No Merge Commit.

Linear history.

---

# 11. Why Companies Prefer Rebase

Without rebase

```text
Merge Login

Merge Dashboard

Merge Payment

Merge Notification

Merge Search
```

History becomes

```text
      M
     / \
----/---\------

     M
    / \
---/---\-------
```

Many unnecessary merge commits.

---

With rebase

```text
Login

Dashboard

Payment

Notification

Search
```

History is straight.

Easy to read.

Easy to debug.

