# 12. Why Push Fails After Rebase?

Before

```text
Remote

B
```

Local after rebase

```text
B'
```

Git thinks

```text
These are different commits.
```

Normal push

```bash
git push
```

fails

Need

```bash
git push --force-with-lease
```

because history changed.

---

# 13. Why --force-with-lease instead of --force?

`--force`

```text
Overwrite everything.
```

Dangerous.

May delete teammates' work.

---

`--force-with-lease`

```text
Overwrite only if remote hasn't changed since I last fetched.
```

Much safer.

Preferred in teams.

---

# 14. Why do we Fetch before Rebase?

```bash
git fetch origin
```

downloads latest commits.

Suppose

Remote

```text
A──C
```

Local

```text
A──B
```

Without fetch

Git doesn't know C exists.

Fetch updates your local view of the remote so rebase has the latest commits to replay onto.

